> When I saw you doing 72 on the radar, I couldn't believe it."  I was
clocked
> doing 72 in a 55 zone, but I'm sure the officer also wanted to pull me
over
> to ask about my Bus.
>
> I recently installed a Jake Raby 2.0L FI engine, and I noticed how much
more
> powerful it was over my old engine.  I was thinking that it would get me
in
> trouble, and I guess I was right.  It was a good check for me, and it was
> also a good check for my speedometer -- it was reading 75 when I passed
the
> officer.
>
> Fortunately, I got off with a written warning, but I now have radar
